## Directory Structure (Feature-First)

```
frontend/src/
├── components/          # Shared, stateless, reusable UI atoms
│   └── *.tsx            # AppHeader, BottomNavBar, RecipeCard …
├── screens/             # Full-page compositions (one per route)
│   └── *Screen.tsx
├── hooks/               # Logic only — no JSX
│   └── use*.ts
├── services/            # HTTP calls only — no state, no JSX
│   └── *Service.ts
├── store/               # Zustand slices — client state only
│   └── use*Store.ts
├── types/               # TypeScript interfaces & Zod schemas
│   └── *.ts
└── utils/               # Pure functions, constants, Colors
    └── colors.ts
```

**MVP rule:** `components/` and `screens/` are enough to ship. Add `hooks/`, `services/`, `store/` only when logic gets reused or files exceed 200 lines.

