## Component Rules

```tsx
// ✅ Named export + explicit props interface
interface RecipeCardProps {
  recipe: Recipe;
  onPress?: () => void;
}

export const RecipeCard: React.FC<RecipeCardProps> = ({ recipe, onPress }) => (
  <TouchableOpacity onPress={onPress} activeOpacity={0.8}>
    ...
  </TouchableOpacity>
);

// ❌ Anonymous default export — untraceable in stack traces
export default ({ recipe }) => <View />;
```

- **Functional components only** — no class components
- File name **matches** export name exactly: `RecipeCard.tsx` → `RecipeCard`
- Max **200 lines** per file — split into sub-components if exceeded
- Props interfaces defined **above** the component, not inline

