## State Management (MVP — pragmatic)

> **MVP mode:** Move fast. Strict boundaries enforced post-MVP.

| State Type | Solution |
|---|---|
| Local UI state | `useState` — default choice |
| Shared / cross-screen state | Zustand slice (ok to store fetched data here for now) |
| Navigation | React Navigation params |
| Form | `useState` or React Hook Form |

```ts
// ✅ MVP: useState for simple fetches
const [stores, setStores] = useState<Store[]>([]);
useEffect(() => { fetchStores().then(setStores); }, []);

// ✅ MVP: Zustand is fine for shared fetched data too
useStoreSlice.setState({ stores });

// 🔜 Post-MVP: migrate server state to React Query
```

