## Async UX Pattern (Fire & Listen)

For any operation >300ms (API call, AI analysis, route computation):

1. **Fire** — trigger API → receive `jobId` or await promise
2. **Feedback** — immediately show skeleton or `ActivityIndicator`
3. **Listen** — if polling: exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s → 8s → 15s max)
4. **Resolve** — update UI; on error: show inline error + retry button

```tsx
// ✅ Always show loading state
const { data, isLoading, isError } = useQuery({ ... });

if (isLoading) return <SkeletonCard />;
if (isError)   return <ErrorBanner onRetry={refetch} />;
return <RecipeCard data={data} />;

// ❌ Silent loading — user sees nothing
const [data, setData] = useState(null);
useEffect(() => { fetchData().then(setData); }, []);
return data ? <RecipeCard data={data} /> : null;
```

