## Accessibility (React Native)

```tsx
// ✅ TouchableOpacity with accessibilityLabel
<TouchableOpacity
  accessibilityLabel="Add salmon to cart"
  accessibilityRole="button"
  onPress={handleAdd}
>
  <MaterialIcons name="add_shopping_cart" />
</TouchableOpacity>

// ❌ View with onPress — not reachable via screen readers
<View onPress={handleAdd}>
  <MaterialIcons name="add_shopping_cart" />
</View>
```

- **Always** use `TouchableOpacity` / `Pressable` — never `View` with `onPress`
- Icon-only buttons **must** have `accessibilityLabel`
- Destructive actions (delete, clear cart) **must** show a confirmation dialog
- Minimum touch target: **44×44pt**
- Text contrast minimum **4.5:1** against its background — check `Colors` pairs
- Test at common screen widths: **375px** (iPhone SE), **390px** (iPhone 14), **412px** (Pixel 7)

